Title: 3/20 Anaerobic/Aerobic LT Test
WorkoutDescription: Warmup: 20 minutes easy in Zones 1 and 2. Ride 3 X 1 minute fast pedaling at 100rpm to get things moving. Ride 5 minutes easy. Perform the test on a relatively flat road or on an indoor trainer. Main Set: Ride 3 minutes ALL OUT BEST EFFORT. Ride easy 10 minutes. Rice 20 min Time Trial BEST EFFORT. Make both of these tests as steady as possible. Do not go too hard at the beginning so that you can't hold a steady effort. Ride any remaining time low zone 2. Cool Down 10 minutes. Record your average heartrate and average normalized power (if using a powermeter) for both the 3 minute and 20 minute efforts.

Title: Bike, Z3 Tempo Strength "Cadence Powerups" [up to 2 hours if you have time]
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 10 minutes easy spinning. Ride 20 minutes in Aerobic Zone 2, then do 4 X 30 second pickups with 1 minute recovery between each. Ride a few minutes easy, hydrate. Bike 8 x 90 second intervals starting in a big gear (close to 75 rpm). Every 30 seconds, try to pick the cadence up at least 5 rpms. So go from 75 to 80 rpms at the 30 second point, 80 to 85 at the minute mark and then max cadence the last 10 seconds. Ride 2 minutes easy between the intervals. Heartrate/power will rise into Tempo Zone 3 and maybe zone 4. Push these Cool down 10 minutes easy spinning.

Title: Run, Tempo Fartlek: Speed Ladders
WorkoutDescription: Tempo Fartlek (alternating speeds) Run. Warmup 10 minutes easy. Include 3 sets of the following ladder: 30 sec fast/30 sec easy 60 sec fast/60 sec easy 90 sec fast/90 sec easy 2 minutes fast *5 minutes easy between sets Fast for this workout is close to your 5K effort/speed, or around 90%. Do not use heartrate for these intervals since they are short in duration. The remainder of the run should be in zones 1-2. Cool down 5 minutes easy.

Title: Supplemental Strength
WorkoutDescription: Do a circuit of 15-20 reps of each exercise. Do the circuit three times through. Start the first round with light weights. Use enough weight that you feel a light burn by the end of the 15-20 reps. Body-weight might be plenty for the leg exercises. Do not go to a heavy burn in your muscles. Shoulder-width Squats (body-weight or dumbell/barbell) Lat Pull Down, standing pull the bar down Tri-cep exercise (kickbacks or other) Lunges, L then R foot forward Seated Row Dead Lifts Core Exercise Can be done at home or a gym. If overly tired, this is the workout to skip in the week. Should take 25-40 minutes depending on rest in between.

Title: Swim, 100s-200-50s {2000}

Title: Bike, Endurance with Cadence Drills
WorkoutDescription: Warmup up 15 minutes easy, 90-95 rpm Ride 6 x 2 minutes of "Cadence Drills" done as: 1 min "on" at 105rpm 1 min "off" at 85rpm Ride 10 minutes easy. Ride 2 x 5 minutes in the top of zone 2/bottom of zone 3. 5 minutes easy in between REPEAT Cadence drills of 6 x 2 minutes as described above. Cooldown 10-15 minutes easy riding. Excluding warmup and cool down, record average HR (even if it's just an estimate) and max HR in your log. If you trained above your Aerobic Zone, try to quantify what you did.
